PSD Layout Grid Generator
Written by Dan Lien [http://danclien.com]
June 19, 2009

Introduction
-------------

This is a script and action file for Adobe Photoshop CS3 that can generate a layout grid based on the 960.gs grid system [http://960.gs].

This has only been tested on Adobe Photoshop CS3 and CS5 for the Mac.


Installation for Mac
---------------------

1. Close Adobe Photoshop.

2. Place the "Layout Grid Generator.jsx" file into your Scripts folder.

   Mac: [Hard drive]/Applications/Adobe Photoshop CS3/Presets/Scripts/
   PC: C:\Program Files\Adobe\Adobe Photoshop CS3\Presets\Scripts\

3. Place the "dclScriptLibrary.atn" file your Actions folder.

   Mac: [Hard drive]/Applications/Adobe Photoshop CS3/Presets/Actions/
   PC: C:\Program Files\Adobe\Adobe Photoshop CS3\Presets\Actions\

4. Open up Adobe Photoshop.

5. Open up the Actions panel, and load up the dclScriptLibrary Action set.


How to Use
-----------

1.  Go to [File] -> [Scripts] -> [Layout Grid Generator].

2.  Changes the values to your preference.

3.  Click "Generate."


